<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
          xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
          xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org"
          xml:lang="en" xml:id="colormap">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>colormap</refname>
        <refpurpose>generates a colormap using a predefined one.</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <synopsis>
            cmap = colormap(cmapfunc)
            cmap = colormap(cmapfunc, cmapSize)
        </synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection role="parameters">
        <title>Arguments</title>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>cmapfunc</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        A string (function name) or a function itself. The predefined map to be used.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>cmapSize</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        The size of the colormap to be generated.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            <literal>colormap</literal> is a helper to generate colormaps (to be set for a figure) by calling dedicated function containing predefined color maps.
        </para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
plot3d();
// Change colormap to parula
gcf().color_map = colormap("parula", 32);
// Change colormap to jet (without using colormap function)
gcf().color_map = jet(32);
// Change colormap to jet (using colormap function)
gcf().color_map = colormap(jet, 64);
            ]]></programlisting>
    </refsection>
    <refsection role="see also">
        <title>See also</title>
        <simplelist type="inline">
            <member>
                <link linkend="colormaps">Using colormaps</link>
            </member>
            <member>
                <link linkend="jet">jet</link>
            </member>
            <member>
                <link linkend="parula">parula</link>
            </member>
        </simplelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection role="history">
        <title>History</title>
        <revhistory>
